# Project: Installing Apache on GCP Linux Server

## Objective
To install and run Apache web server on a Linux Virtual Machine in Google Cloud.

## Services Used
- Google Compute Engine (Linux VM)
- VPC Network
- Firewall rules (HTTP)

## Steps I Followed
1. Created a Linux VM in Google Cloud.
2. Connected to the VM using SSH.
3. Updated system packages.
4. Installed Apache web server.
5. Accessed Apache default page using VM's external IP.

## Commands Used
(See commands.txt file)

## Proof (Screenshots)
- apache-vm-details.png → VM details page  
- apache-ssh.png → SSH access to VM  
- apache-install-command.png → Installing Apache  
- apache-running.png → Apache default page in browser

## What I Learned
- How to install software on a Linux server.
- How Apache works as a web server.
- How firewall rules affect web access.
- How to access a web server using public IP.

## Next Steps
- Host a custom HTML website instead of default Apache page.
